Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Zest and halve the @lemon{1}. Cut the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, crack the @egg{1} into a medium #bowl{} and whisk. Put the @panko breadcrumbs{50%g} and @curry powder mix{1} into another bowl. Season with @salt{1/2%tsp} and pepper.

Season the @British chicken thighs{3}, then dip into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated.

Transfer to a clean plate.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough oil to coat the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan and fry until golden-brown, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Transfer the chicken to a baking tray and bake on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

In the meantime, trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, then separate the leaves. Keep a couple whole leaves aside for each burger and thinly slice the rest widthways.

In a large bowl, add the @coleslaw mix{120%g}, a third of the @mayonnaise{96%g} and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper.

When the wedges are at least halfway through cooking, toss the lemon zest through and return to the oven for the remaining cooking time.

== Sauce ==

In a medium bowl, mix together the remaining mayonnaise, @korma curry paste{50%g} and @mango chutney{40%g}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

== To Serve ==

Halve the @burger buns{2}. Pop them onto the chicken baking tray and into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Just before you're ready to serve, toss the baby gem through the coleslaw.

Transfer the bun bases to your plates and spread over the korma sauce. Add the fried chicken pieces and top with the whole baby gem leaves. Spoon over any remaining sauce, then sandwich on the bun lids.

Serve with the wedges and coleslaw alongside. Enjoy!